## Difficulty Rating Criteria

Rate the difficulty of the decisions in this hand as "easy", "medium", or "hard" based on these factors:

**Hard situations** (notorious blackjack dilemmas):
- Player 16 vs dealer 10 (hit and likely bust, stand and likely lose)
- Player 12-13 vs dealer 2-3 (borderline hit/stand)
- Player 15 vs dealer 10 (classic hard decision)
- Soft 18 vs dealer 9-A (hit a seemingly good hand?)
- Any hand requiring multiple consecutive draws without busting

**Medium situations:**
- Player 12-16 vs dealer 7-9 (clear basic strategy says hit, but bust risk is real)
- Player 10-11 double down decisions (clear action but stakes are doubled)

**Easy situations:**
- Player 17+ (always stand, no decision)
- Player 8 or less (always hit, no bust risk)
- Player 20-21 (trivially stand)
- Dealer busts regardless of player action

